{
  "stem": "2074.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They're sleeping on floors in synagogues and in other Jewish public places.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they are entitled to get out and go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you go home and wait.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We had no choice.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We went home.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They took another couple from Germany, a couple-- just a girl and a boy, and married them-- fiction marriage, that two can go on the same certificate on our place.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They took off for Israel, and we had to come back.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] So after you found out that your husband had been killed, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] what-- what happened in your life then?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You had the baby.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I stayed for a while in-- in the city where I lived in, my apartment.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And after a while, I went back to my parents with the baby.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't want to be alone in the city.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Horochow was a big ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's set-- 1941, the Germans marched in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the first thing they did it, first month, the Ukrainians demanded from the German government to give them the SS group.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And one month later, they came from house-- that was 1941-- from house to house, where it was a young Jewish man or middle aged man, take him out.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they told us they'd taken him to labor.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we hoped that it was labor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were bringing us false letters, the Ukrainians, with lies in order to take money, whatever.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They-- they took all the young people out as I found out when I came back.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The mayor told me that there was another grave of these all the young men.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
